data.enText: dislike of or opposition to a plan, an idea, etc.; refusal to obey

data.chText: 和所有的新观念一样，它受到了抵制。
data.enText: As with all new ideas it met with resistance.

data.chText: 这项新的法规已经遇到很多的抵制。
data.enText: There has been a lot of resistance to this new law.

data.chText: 对变革的抵制几乎毁了这个行业。
data.enText: Resistance to change has nearly destroyed the industry.
the act of using force to oppose sb/sth

data.chText: 保卫者进行了顽强的抵抗。
data.enText: The defenders put up a strong resistance .

data.chText: 示威者几乎没有对警察进行任何反抗。
data.enText: The demonstrators offered little or no resistance to the police.
the power not to be affected by sth

data.chText: 艾滋病降低了身体的抗感染能力。
data.enText: AIDS lowers the body's resistance to infection.
a force that stops sth moving or makes it move more slowly
wind/air resistance (= in the design of planes or cars)
the opposition of a piece of electrical equipment, etc. to the flow of a direct current

simple_means.memory_skill: resist 反抗 + ance 状态，性质，状况 → 反抗；抵抗力

means: （尤指敌占区的）秘密抵抗组织

data.enText: (choose, follow, take, etc.) the line of least resistance
(to choose, etc.) the easiest way of doing sth

tr: the action of opposing something that you disapprove or disagree with
example: he encountered a general feeling of resistance from many citizens
despite opposition from the newspapers he went ahead

tr: the military action of resisting the enemy's advance
group action in opposition to those in power
an electrical device that resists the flow of electrical current
(psychiatry) an unwillingness to bring repressed feelings into conscious awareness
the degree of unresponsiveness of a disease-causing microorganism to antibiotics or other drugs (as in penicillin-resistant bacteria)
a secret group organized to overthrow a government or occupation force
any mechanical force that tends to retard or oppose motion
a material's opposition to the flow of electric current
the capacity of an organism to defend itself against harmful environmental agents
example: these trees are widely planted because of their resistance to salt and smog

tr: (medicine) the condition in which an organism can resist disease

value.def: Resistance to something such as a change or a new idea is a refusal to accept it.

example.ex: The US wants big cuts in European agricultural export subsidies, but this is meeting resistance.
example.tran: 美国想大幅度削减欧洲农业出口补贴，但此举遭到了抵制。

value.def: Resistance to an attack consists of fighting back against the people who have attacked you.

example.ex: The troops are encountering stiff resistance...
Police in riot gear cleared the noisy demonstrators, who offered no resistance.
example.tran: 身穿防暴服的警察驱散了喧闹的游行者，没有遇到抵抗。

value.def: The resistance of your body to germs or diseases is its power to remain unharmed or unaffected by them.

example.ex: This disease is surprisingly difficult to catch as most people have a natural resistance to it.
example.tran: 由于多数人对这种病具有天然免疫力，所以发病率低得出奇。

value.def: Wind or air resistance is a force which slows down a moving object or vehicle.

example.ex: The design of the bicycle has managed to reduce the effects of wind resistance and drag.
example.tran: 这种自行车的设计成功地减少了风的阻力和摩擦力。

value.def: In electrical engineering or physics, resistance is the ability of a substance or an electrical circuit to stop the flow of an electrical current through it.

example.ex: ...materials that lose all their electrical resistance.

value.def: In a country which is occupied by the army of another country, or which has a very harsh and strict government, the resistance is an organized group of people who are involved in illegal activities against the people in power.

example.ex: They managed to escape after being arrested by the resistance.
example.tran: 他们被抵抗组织抓住后又设法逃脱了。

value.tran: （被他国军队占领或被专制政府统治的国家中的）抵抗组织，地下组织

value.def: If you take the line of least resistance in a situation, you do what is easiest, even though you think that it may not be the right thing to do. In American English, you usually talk about the path of least resistance .

example.ex: They would rather take the line of least resistance than become involved in arguments.
example.tran: 他们倾向采用阻力最小的方案，不愿卷入纷争。

value.tran: 阻力最小的路线;最容易的途径
